{{Quote|The holocrons contain the most closely guarded secrets of the Jedi Order.|[[Jocasta Nu]]|<ref name="Holocron Heist" />}}
'''Jedi holocrons''' were [[Jedi]] artifacts used to store information and teachings of the [[Jedi Order]].<ref name="Holocron Heist" /> [[Holocron]]s were constructed with a security mechanism<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> preventing non-[[Force-sensitive]] individuals from opening them and accessing the secrets held within.<ref name="Cargo of Doom">{{TCW|Cargo of Doom}}</ref> The teachings contained in Jedi holocrons were typically relayed to whomever opened them as an interactive [[hologram]], appearing as the [[Jedi Master]] who had recorded the information. Sharing the knowledge found in Jedi holocrons with those who were not members of the Jedi Order was discouraged, as the majority of holocrons contained data relating to the nature and applications of [[the Force]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> Holocrons were stored within the [[Holocron Vault]], located within the [[Jedi Archives]] of the [[Imperial Palace|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant]]. Access to the Vault was only permitted to Jedi who currently serve on the [[Jedi High Council]].<ref name="Holocron Heist" />

[[File:Jedi_Holocron_SWDConv.png|thumb|left|220px|A elderly female Jedi holds a Jedi holocron]]
Many holocrons could only be unlocked when paired with a [[memory crystal]],<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> such as the [[Kyber memory crystal]], entrusted to the [[Rodian]] Jedi Master [[Bolla Ropal]] during the [[Clone Wars]], which contained a list of all known Force-sensitive [[youngling]]s. The [[bounty hunter]] [[Cad Bane]], under the employ of the [[Sith Lord]] [[Darth Sidious]],<ref name="Holocron Heist" /> [[Battle of Devaron|captured]] Ropal and acquired the Kyber crystal<ref name="Cargo of Doom" /> after previously [[Raid on the Jedi Temple|stealing]] a holocron from the Jedi temple.<ref name="Holocron Heist" /> Ropal refused to unlock the crystal's data for Bane, however Bane soon managed to force [[Jedi Knight]] [[Anakin Skywalker]] to open the holocron for him after capturing his [[Padawan]], [[Ahsoka Tano]].<ref name="Cargo of Doom" />

Later in the war, Jedi Master [[Depa Billaba]] owned a [[Kanan Jarrus' holocron|holocron]] which she passed onto her apprentice, [[Kanan Jarrus|Caleb Dume]], after the conclusion of the [[Battle of Kaller|Conquest of Kaller]]<ref name="Kanan 1" /> and shortly before her [[Death|demise]] during the [[Great Jedi Purge]] after [[Order 66]] was activated by [[Darth Sidious]].<ref name="Kanan 2">[[Kanan 2|''Kanan'' 2]]</ref> It was used by him, [[Ezra Bridger]], and [[Ahsoka Tano]] up until [[2 BBY]] when it was destroyed whilst being [[Holocron fusion|merged]] with a [[Sith holocron (Malachor)|Sith holocron]].<ref name="Holocrons of Fate">{{Rebels|The Holocrons of Fate}}</ref><ref name="Visions and Voices">{{Rebels|Visions and Voices}}</ref>

[[Crime lord]] [[Grakkus Jahibakti Tingi|Grakkus]] the [[Hutt]] collected many Jedi artifacts after the Great Jedi Purge, including holocrons, which he stored in [[Palace of Grakkus the Hutt|his palace]] on [[Nar Shaddaa]].<ref name="Star Wars 9">[[Star Wars (2015) 9|''Star Wars'' (2015) 9]]</ref>

